   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Steps to reproduce the bug:\r\n1. Run `bitcoin-qt`\r\n2. If `Options -> Window -> Hide tray icon` is unchecked, check it and press `OK`\r\n3. Uncheck `Hide tray icon` and press `OK`\r\n4. The appearing tray icon is unusable: neither the icon can be activated by the left-click nor a context menu shows by the right-click.\r\n\r\nKubuntu 18.04.1 LTS\r\nKDE Plasma 5.12.7\r\nQt 5.9.5\r\n\r\nAlmost always there is an error message in `debug.log`:\r\n```\r\nGUI: QXcbConnection: XCB error: 3 (BadWindow), sequence: 4609, resource id: 50336490, major code: 40 (TranslateCoords), minor code: 0\r\n```",
